collections.name: american snout
collections.description:
Butterfly: Wingspan: 1¼ - 2 inches (3.5 - 5 cm) UPPER SIDE (dorsal) Brown with orange patches; white spots on brown forewing tip. UNDER SURFACE (ventral) Forewing has orange patch near body; dark tip with white spots. Hindwing (light form) gray brown. Hindwing (dark form) mottled violet and gray. Palps long and extended forward. Forewing tip squared off. Scalloped hindwing edge. The overwintering stage.

ID Tip: Look for elongated “snout” (palps) and squared forewing tips.

Egg: White. Round. Laid singly on host, often on new leaf tips.

Caterpillar: Light green; numerous small yellow dots; yellow lateral stripes on back and sides Two small black dots on thorax. Slender and worm-like.

Chrysalis: Green, tiny pale-yellow dots on back. Yellow lines form "Y" on upper body. Often suspended from underside of hackberry leaf.

Philosophy and Creation Process
This artwork is not just an image; it is a portal to the depths of the human subconscious. The visual presents

existence. This is more than just a piece of artit is an intuitive experience.

of awareness. This infinite cycle represents humanitys search for itselfa journey of the soul. The spiral forms

collections.name: MetaMKT
collections.description: “CRYpto: The Emotional Market” is a stunning visual narrative of Bitcoin’s volatility, created specifically for NFT.NY 2025. This piece overlays the iconic BTC price chart with bold, swirling effects that accidentally reveal the silhouette of a kneeling figure, expressing market sentiments that accompany each price swing. Through dynamic colors and abstract movement, this artwork captures both the euphoria of meteoric rises and the anguish of devastating panics. It stands as a poignant reminder that behind every price chart is an emotional journey — one defined by resilience, ambition, and the relentless drive to forge the future of finance.

This collection weaves the wrath of approaching storms with the grace of fleeting light, offering a meditative reflection on resilience, transformation, and the eternal dance of elements. Every image is a portal into the sublime — a moment suspended in the ether, where time slows and nature speaks.

collections.name: No Exits Found
collections.description:
Each piece captures a moment too raw for language: the scream before the sob, the instant between breath and breakdown, the split-second of pure, holy rage.

Pulled from the edges of panic, performance, and existential dread, these works were made to haunt the viewer. Loud without sound. Bleeding without blood.

This is not expression. This is exorcism.
There is no exit. Only echoes.
